    "department": "People \u0026 Talent",
    "description": "Reporting Manager: CFO\nLocation: Mumbai (onsite / hybrid)\n\n\nAbout Nivoda\nAt Nivoda, we’re transforming the diamond and jewelry industry with the largest digital\nmarketplace of its kind. We bridge timeless luxury with cutting-edge technology, enabling faster, smarter, and more connected transactions on a global scale. With teams in London, New York, Hong Kong, and Mumbai, we’ve experienced unprecedented growth, doubling revenue year over year.\nAs we continue to scale, our people remain the cornerstone of our success. That’s why we’re\nsearching for a HRBP to drive exceptional employee experiences and build strong, scalable\npeople programs that empower our global teams. Reporting to the Vice President People, this\nrole will be central to strengthening our HR foundations and creating strategies that enhance\nengagement, development, and organisational success.\n\nAbout the Role\nThe HRBP will be instrumental in delivering a best-in-class HR experience, from onboarding to performance management and development. This leader will optimise and scale HR practices to align with Nivoda’s ambitious growth trajectory, fostering an environment where employees thrive and contribute to the company’s mission of doubling revenue annually. This is an opportunity for an experienced, strategic HR professional who is equally comfortable in high-level planning and hands-on execution, and who thrives in a fast-paced, global environment.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\nBuild Scalable HR Programs and Processes\n● Develop and implement people-centric programs across the employee lifecycle,\nincluding onboarding, performance management, and career development.\n\n● Ensure HR operations comply with regional regulations while maintaining the agility\nrequired in a high-growth organisation.\n\n● Evaluate and implement tools and technologies to optimise HR processes and enhance\nthe employee experience.\n\n● Drive Employee Engagement and Retention\n\n● Design and execute initiatives to foster employee engagement, satisfaction, and\nwell-being.\n\n● Build frameworks for professional development, succession planning, and career\nprogression to support Nivoda’s culture of continuous growth.\n\n● Champion diversity, equity, and inclusion across all HR strategies and initiatives.\n\n\n\n\nCollaborate with Leadership\n● Partner with leaders across departments to understand business needs and implement\nHR solutions that drive results.\n\n● Act as a trusted advisor to the VP People and senior leadership, contributing to the\ndevelopment and execution of the overall people strategy.\n\n● Provide data-driven insights to inform strategic decisions, including workforce planning\nand employee performance metrics. Lead with Excellence and Integrity.\n\n● Establish a culture of accountability, continuous improvement, and operational\nexcellence.\n\n● Manage HR compliance, ensuring adherence to local laws and regulations while\nmaintaining ethical and inclusive practices.\n\n● Monitor HR trends and best practices, bringing innovative solutions to the organisation.\n\n\nWhat We’re Looking For\nWe’re looking for an HR leader who combines strategic thinking with an ability to execute and deliver results.\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n● 5 - 7 years in HR or related roles with demonstrated expertise in global HR practices.\n\n● Proven experience in high-growth organisations, ideally in tech, marketplace, or\ncustomer-centric industries.\n\n● Strong knowledge of HR systems, compliance, and analytics.\n\n● Exceptional project management skills with a track record of implementing impactful HR\ninitiatives.\n\n● Excellent interpersonal and communication skills with a collaborative mindset.\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n● Experience working with distributed teams across North America, Europe, and Asia.\n\n● Background in luxury, technology, or fast-paced global industries.\n\n● Demonstrated success in scaling HR programs to align with organisational growth.\n\nWhat You’ll Get\nJoin Nivoda and be part of a team that powers extraordinary growth and innovation. Help shape our people strategy while advancing your career in an environment that values creativity, collaboration, and results. We’re excited to see the impact you’ll make!",
